Description: Here we have an Ibanex GIO GRX 45 model. Original black knobs have been replaced with gun metal grey ones. 22 frets, stock pickups - 1 humbucker and 2 single coils. 5 way selector switch and volume and tone knobs. This is definetly a beginner guitar, and was the guitar I first learned on 15+ years ago (for what that's worth). Buy it at a fair price for your kid who is just starting out. Some very small scratches and dings. Most notably the area behind the bridge where a sticker was scraped off, however it is hardly noticeable in regular light at a short distance. The "GIO" on the headstock was blacked out with a sharpie to make it look a bit classier. Nice looking without busting the bank. It is a comfortable guitar and plays well enough for what it is, a great learning guitar. Frets are not worn down at all, never been filed and have a LOT of life left in them. Works good. Includes a whammy bar. Free shipping to the lower 48. Will ship very securely..! No returns. Thanks for looking..!
Title: Ibanez GRX 45 Electric Guitar Beginner
